Parks a train in a free slot (if available) and enqueues it for spawning. Used by recovery save
import where there may be more trains than depot slots. Trains without a slot still spawn correctly;
they just won't appear in the depot UI while waiting.

member.remarks:
 The sim loop events are invoked as follows:

 // Process commands
	UpdateBeforeCmdProc()
	(ProcessCommands)
 UpdateAfterCmdProc()

 if (paused) {
		ReadGameStateFrequent()
 } else {
		UpdateAfterSync()

		for (number of sim steps based on game speed) {
			if (current step > 0) {
 			// Process commands
				UpdateBeforeCmdProc()
				(ProcessCommands)
				UpdateAfterCmdProc()
			}

			UpdateStart()
			ParallelUpdateStart()
			Update()
			ParallelUpdateEnd()
			UpdateEnd()
			ReadGameStateFrequent()
		}
 }

 UpdateEndForUi()

member.example:
This is intended use of the WaitHelper class.

WaitHelper waiter;

bool SearchSomething() {
	if (waiter.WaitOne()) {
		return false; // Waiting.
	}

	if (search()) {
		waiter.ResetExtraWaitTime(); // Resets retries and wait time.
		return true; // Success.
	} else if (waiter.StartWait(true)) {
		return false;
	} else {
		waiter.ResetExtraWaitTime();
		return true; // Max retries was reached, do something about it!
	}
}

member.summary:
 Annotate a readonly string member to have it provide name for its
 parent object. This allows to properly show object titles in lists
 and dictionaries. Example use:

 public class Feature {
		[EditorClassName]
		public string FeatureName => "Mountain";
 }

 Can be added to a text or number editor to provide it with secondary source of validation result.
 IMPORTANT: The validation result is only queried on editor rebuild.
 For more lightweight applications, check 

 Example use:
 [EditorValidationSource(nameof(CodeValidationResult))]
 public string CustomCode { get; private set; }
 public string CodeValidationResult => !CustomCode.StartsWith("namespace")
		? $"This must start with namespace." : null;
